issue.title: [CF 938] Error loading Interface\AddOns\TellMeWhen
issue.body:
--Low Priority--

I usually look through all tickets to see if my issue has been brought up. If so, sorry. 937 is to many to look through :P.

What version of TellMeWhen are you using?  6.2.6-314-gef4c603

Do you have an error log of what happened?

5:37:09.478  Loading add-on TellMeWhen
3/25 05:37:09.478  ** Loading table of contents Interface\AddOns\TellMeWhen\TellMeWhen.toc
3/25 05:37:09.478  Error loading Interface\AddOns\TellMeWhen\Localization\TellMeWhen-deDE.lua
3/25 05:37:09.478  Error loading Interface\AddOns\TellMeWhen\Localization\TellMeWhen-esMX.lua
3/25 05:37:09.478  Error loading Interface\AddOns\TellMeWhen\Localization\TellMeWhen-koKR.lua
3/25 05:37:09.478  Error loading Interface\AddOns\TellMeWhen\Localization\TellMeWhen-ptBR.lua
3/25 05:37:09.478  Error loading Interface\AddOns\TellMeWhen\Localization\TellMeWhen-itIT.lua

Please provide any additional information below.

This is a log in error from World of Warcraft\Logs\FrameXML.  I have tried deleting WTF folder and Interface, Installed TellMeWhen uninstall and re-install again.

Best addon around and awsome job!!!


> Posted by CurseForge user Shaft840 | Imported from CurseForge issue #938 | Raw

comments.body:
Thanks. Those are non-critical errors - they shouldn't be causing you any issues at all. Regardless, it means that I forgot to remove those from the load order when I disabled those localizations (because they are grossly incomplete), so thanks for pointing it out!


> Posted by CurseForge user Cybeloras

Your right it didn't cause any problems, just osding out. Could help faster load time by like .001 though :P. All my addons are killing my load time :( and no problem.


> Posted by CurseForge user Shaft840

Changed in f1edcfa. Change will be included in the next packaged build. Thanks!


> Posted by CurseForge user Cybeloras
